<span class="displaytext">the (candidate full) campaign today announced that (PARTY NAME) operative kelly adams will serve as the campaign's south carolina state director. <p>"kelly is a talented organizer with deep roots in the palmetto state, and i'm delighted she's going to run our south carolina campaign," (candidate last) said. </p><p>adams most recently served as director of the south carolina house (PARTY NAME) caucus, where she helped craft the caucus' legislative agenda and developed an aggressive fundraising and candidate recruitment program. prior to that, adams was a field organizer for the national association of social workers and south carolina deputy director of howard dean's 2004 presidential campaign. </p><p>as state director, adams will oversee the day-to-day operations of (candidate last)'s south carolina primary campaign. </p><p>"at a critical time in our nation's history, senator (candidate last) has the experience and vision to get this country back on the right track, and repair america's image in the world," adams said. "senator (candidate last) represents leadership and government we can trust."</p></span>



